>  Is it worth replacing the needle bearings in the beam?  If so is there a 
> tool that makes the bearing easy to replace?

Hi Paul,
Replace them only if they need to be replaced.  So inspect first.  The shop 
manual tool slides them out like a body dent puller, but without damaging 
them.
